item.title: Iterators
item.description: Iterators # What is an Iterator # An iterator is an object that provides sequential access to values in an iterable one by one. While you may not see the use of them at the moment, the benefits of using them will be explained a bit later in these sets of notes. iter(iterable) returns an iterator over the elements of iterable. next(<iter>) returns the next element in an iterator.
